00:00:17.440 --> 00:00:19.440
Chocolate Wafers  Recipe

00:00:19.580 --> 00:00:21.760
250g margarine (or butter)

00:00:21.760 --> 00:00:23.760
400g sugar

00:00:23.960 --> 00:00:25.960
360g sour cream

00:00:26.180 --> 00:00:28.580
10g vanilla sugar

00:00:28.780 --> 00:00:31.240
60g dark chocolate

00:00:31.400 --> 00:00:33.400
300g ground bicuits ( Bambiâ€™s Lane Ground Biscuits)

00:00:33.540 --> 00:00:35.600
1 packet of wafer sheets (5 wafer sheets)

00:00:37.020 --> 00:00:42.020
Place 250g of margarine  in a saucepan

00:00:42.160 --> 00:00:44.260
Cook over low heat stirring with a wooden spoon

00:01:09.340 --> 00:01:14.360
After 1 min add 400 g of sugar and continue to stir

00:01:54.260 --> 00:01:56.840
then add 60 g of dark chocolate and continue to stir

00:02:17.200 --> 00:02:21.140
add 360g of sour cream

00:03:00.080 --> 00:03:04.460
add 10 g of vanilla sugar

00:03:20.060 --> 00:03:23.520
and after  approximately 8 to 10 minutes everything is melted end well combined.

00:03:24.140 --> 00:03:26.560
Add 300g of ground biscuits and stir a little

00:03:52.440 --> 00:03:55.080
Remove from heat

00:03:55.420 --> 00:03:57.500
And continue to stir until well combined.

00:03:57.760 --> 00:04:00.560
Then leave and allow it to cool until lukewarm

00:04:15.880 --> 00:04:18.860
take one wafer sheet

00:04:19.140 --> 00:04:22.040
Make sure the smooth side of the wafer sheet is facing up.

00:04:30.500 --> 00:04:37.060
And spread the mixture evenly over entire wafer.sheet with the back of a metal spoon.

00:04:47.400 --> 00:04:52.880
Try to estimate the amount of mixture and make sure there is enough to fill four times.

00:06:04.920 --> 00:06:10.100
Lay onother wafer sheet and repeat previous step until all wafer sheets are used up

00:07:06.500 --> 00:07:13.020
Take care to finish with a sheet of wafer (waffled side up) and not the mixture.

00:07:35.880 --> 00:07:40.100
Place a tray over and put something heavy to help wafers adhere to each other

00:07:40.300 --> 00:07:43.640
Leave it to set for at least 6 hours  or overnight.

00:07:44.240 --> 00:07:48.920
Cut into diamond shapes before serving.

